# SMB

## 1️ SMB Overview

- SMB = network file/resource sharing protocol.
    
- Windows → native support; Samba → Linux/Unix implementation (SMB/CIFS).
    
- Ports:
    
    - SMB1/CIFS → TCP 137,138,139
        
    - SMB2/3 → TCP 445
        
- ACLs govern access (read, write, execute) per share.
    

---

## 2️ Samba Basics

- Key daemons: `smbd` (file/print services), `nmbd` (NetBIOS/IPC).
    
- Samba can act as:
    
    - Standalone server
        
    - Active Directory domain member
        
    - Domain controller (Samba 4+)
        
- Workgroups organize SMB hosts.
    

---

## 3️ Default Samba Config Example

`[global] workgroup = DEV.INFREIGHT.HTB server string = DEVSMB log file = /var/log/samba/log.%m max log size = 1000 map to guest = bad user usershare allow guests = yes  [printers] comment = All Printers path = /var/spool/samba printable = yes guest ok = no read only = yes create mask = 0700  [print$] comment = Printer Drivers path = /var/lib/samba/printers browseable = yes read only = yes guest ok = no`

**Dangerous settings to watch:**

- `browseable = yes` → attacker can list share contents
    
- `guest ok = yes` → anonymous access allowed
    
- `writable = yes` + `create mask = 0777` → full write permissions
    

